<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-72-0109 </DOCNO><TEXT>In recent years biotechnology has undergone exciting advances. This fascinatingfield covers not only the new genetic engineering techniques but alsoold fermentation processes which our ancestors practised thousands ofyears ago. With this book the reader will gain insight into the processesand products involved. The basics of biotechnology are explained in eightinformation-packed chapters. Topics explored include microorganisms,metabolic pathways, process control, product recovery and bioreactors.</TEXT></DOC>